# Crab Bucatini
# Had this amazing but straight forward crab bucatini breakfast pasta at this cafe call Dish & Spoon in Camberwell, Melbourne.
# Served with a side of toasted sourdough bread, the star is the sauce. 
# But given it's a breakfast spot, I suspect costings limited how much crab meat and caviar can be added - which always left me in want. 
# So this is my homage to that dish, without the limitations.

Ingredients

Main Ingredients

Bucatini


Sauce Base
Cherry tomatoes
Roasted capsicum
Red chilli, deseeded
100ml kombu dashi 

Crab Stock Base

2 pounds crab carcasses or any combo of shells, legs, claws and bodies
2 quarts water or enough to cover carcasses
1 medium yellow onion roughly chopped
2 stalks celery roughly chopped
3 to 4 cloves garlic roughly chopped
3 to 4 sprigs thyme
1 teaspoon black peppercorns
1 bay leaf
Ginger
Parsley
Sea salt to taste





Garnish
Shiso, midrib removed, fine chiffonade
Caviar, my choice osetra caviar, but any really except 
